messages.messageBody:
Dear listmembers,

Just to inform you of the new republication of :
Documents and Studies on 19th c. Monetary History, Japan,
Republication of The Currency of Japan, A Reprint of Articles, Letters, and
Official Reports, Published at Intervals in the Foreign Newspapers of
Japan, together with Translations from Japanese Journals, Relating to the
Currency, Paper and Metallic, of the Empire of Japan (Yokohama, 1882),
M. Kovalchuk, G. Depeyrot, ed., 2011, 204 p..

In the collection Moneta (<http://www.moneta.be>www.moneta.be), number 121.

You ill find a Japanese translation of the abstract on the website.

Best




Georges Depeyrot,
Archeologies d'Orient et d'Occident, Ecole Normale Superieure, Paris
(CNRS/ENS/UMR 8546)

ON LINE : COST project 2010 (with video)..............................
www.emu-cost.net
